content: Just had coffee with a former mentor. Discussed AI in trading, got some book recommendations. Feeling motivated.
Applied to three quant trading firms today. Each application tailored to showcase my Python skills and market analysis experience.
Set up a Python environment for machine learning. Experimenting with basic models for market prediction.
Received a call back from one of the firms. They liked my approach to $XVI integration in trading. Interview next week!
Met with a new group of traders. Shared insights on $XVI tokenomics and got some feedback. Networking is paying off.
Spent the last few days refining my trading model. Incorporated insights from recent discussions. Seeing improvements.

Joined a local AI meetup. Learned about new trends in AI-driven trading algorithms. This community feels like home.
Got an email from a friend at a blockchain startup. They're looking for someone with my skill set.

Worked on integrating $XVI into my trading strategy. It's challenging but feels right.
Turned down a job offer from a less-than-ideal firm. Sometimes you have to say no to find your yes.
Spent the last few days exploring smart contracts. Thinking about building a dApp that incorporates $XVI.

Learning the ropes of the new job while still refining my trading strategy. Balancing work and passion.

Reflecting on the past 4 months. From job hunting to securing a position, the journey has been real.

Had a breakthrough in my model's predictive accuracy. Small victories keep me going.
Conversations with my new colleagues have sparked ideas for a side project. Might explore it further.
